The sentencing of former African National Congress Youth League (ANCYL) inner city branch chair Patrick Wisani has been scheduled for December 12 for the murder of his girlfriend.The date was set in the High Court sitting at the Randburg Magistrate&#8217;s Court on Tuesday.Wisani was found guilty on Monday for beating his intimate partner Nosipho Mandleleni with a sjambok and broomstick in September 2015, leading to her death.Wisani was also found guilty of the lesser charges of assault and intimidation of state witness and Nosipho s twin sister, Siphokazi and of her friend Zimbini Mathibe in May 2016.Wisani s trial came to an end in August after the presiding officer Judge Andre Louw recused himself which made him to represent himself in the trial.-TNA Reporter